      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHARIVARI (2) is a consistent gelding who has placed the last four times he has raced here, each of those coming over this distance. Did a good job to come from the back row and finish third last time, beaten 2 metres. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw so could break through. KINKY NZ (12) came from this barrier to win here last month and could be close to another success after she finished runner-up to a handy one last start, beaten 2 metres. With an ounce of luck she is capable of running another big race. HOLY HECKA NZ (10) had a tough draw when resuming but should enjoy a nice trail this time and strikes at 50 per cent when second up so look for improvement. WHEN IN VEGAS (8) must be respected after he raced three wide without cover from this barrier last time but toughed out a narrow win.",
